{"portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": null, "keywords": "map, plan, chart, canada, history, cartography ", "data_series_issue_identification": "001028", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "History and Archaeology  Histoire et arch\u00e9ologie", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "quarterly", "title": "Maps, Plans and Charts of Canada", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Depuis leur cr\u00e9ation en 1872, les Archives nationales du Canada, maintenant Biblioth\u00e8que et Archives Canada, acqui\u00e8rent, conservent et comm\u00e9morent le patrimoine cartographique du Canada. Aujourd'hui, ces fonds renferment plus de 2 millions de pi\u00e8ces. L'instrument de recherche suivant permet aux chercheurs de consulter environ 40 000 descriptions \u00e0 la pi\u00e8ce du \u00ab vieux catalogue sur fiches \u00bb. Ces documents sont d\u00e9crits dans la langue du cr\u00e9ateur; la plupart des descriptions n'existent qu'en anglais.", "id": "", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/obj/900/f11/001028_20100929.xml", "language": "English | Anglais", "resource_type": "Dataset", "format": "XML"}, {"url": "ftp://arcdm20.tor.ec.gc.ca/pub/dist/climate/CWEEDS_2005/ZIPPED%20FILES/ENGLISH/", "language": "French | Fran\\u00e7ais", "resource_type": "Dataset", "format": "XML"}], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2004-03-31", "time_period_coverage_start": "1872", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "1995", "language": "", "url": "", "notes": "Since its inception in 1872, the National Archives of Canada, now Library and Archives Canada, has acquired, preserved and commemorated the cartographic heritage of Canada and there are now some two million items in the collection. This search tool provides access to approximately 40,000 item-level descriptions from the \"old map card catalogue.\" The item-level descriptions are written in the language of the original map, plan, or chart; the majority of the descriptions are written in English.", "owner_org": "75BDAB68-199F-4C06-92A3-E1E6769B0B8E", "keywords_fra": "carte, plan, charte, canada, histoire, cartographie", "resource_type": "file", "department_number": ""}
{"portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": null, "keywords": "temperature data ", "data_series_issue_identification": "", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "Economics and Industry  \u00c9conomie et industrie", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "title": "Canadian Weather Year for Energy Calculation (CWEC)", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Ensembles de donn\u00e9es cr\u00e9\u00e9es en combinant 12 mois m\u00e9t\u00e9orologiques types choisis \u00e0 partir d'une base de donn\u00e9es couvrant habituellement 30 ans de donn\u00e9es des FMCEG. Les mois sont choisis par une comparaison statistique des moyennes mensuelles individuelles et des moyennes mensuelles \u00e0 long terme au regard du rayonnement global quotidien total, des temp\u00e9ratures du thermom\u00e8tre sec moyennes, minimales et maximales, des temp\u00e9ratures du point de ros\u00e9e moyennes, minimales et maximales ainsi que des vitesses du vent moyennes et maximales.\n", "id": "", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2010-04-22", "time_period_coverage_start": "1953-01-01", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_f.html?&", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "2005-01-01", "language": "", "url": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_e.html", "notes": "Datasets created by joining twelve Typical Meteorological Months selected from a database of, usually, 30 years of CWEEDS data. The months are chosen by statistically comparing individual monthly means with long term monthly means for daily total global radiation, mean, minimum and maximum dry bulb temperature, mean, minimum and maximum dew point temperature, and mean and maximum wind speed.\n", "owner_org": "49E2ADF4-AD7A-43EB-85C8-6433D37ED62C", "keywords_fra": "donn\u00e9es de temp\u00e9rature", "resource_type": "file", "department_number": ""}
{"portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": null, "keywords": "sedimentology", "data_series_issue_identification": "", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "Nature and Environment  Nature et environnement", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "title": "GISE Database: Geoinformation on Sediment", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Contient toutes les donn\u00e9es physiques et chimiques sur les s\u00e9diments pour le fleuve et le golfe Saint-Laurent depuis les ann\u00e9es 1970. Ces donn\u00e9es scientifiques proviennent de travaux d'\u00e9chantillonnage, de caract\u00e9risations des s\u00e9diments et d'\u00e9valuations environnementales de projets de dragage.\n", "id": "", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2010-04-22", "time_period_coverage_start": "1970-01-01", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "http://www.ec.gc.ca/stl/default.asp?lang=Fr&n=1AFCE12D-1", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "language": "", "url": "http://www.ec.gc.ca/stl/default.asp?lang=En&n=1AFCE12D-1", "notes": "Contains all the physical and chemical data on the sediment taken from the St. Lawrence River and Gulf since the 1970s. These scientific data originate from sampling work, sediment characterizations and environmental assessments of dredging projects.\n", "owner_org": "49E2ADF4-AD7A-43EB-85C8-6433D37ED62C", "keywords_fra": "s\u00e9dimentologie", "resource_type": "file", "department_number": ""}
{"portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": null, "keywords": "ice thickness, canadian ice service, arctic water resources\n", "data_series_issue_identification": "", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "Nature and Environment  Nature et environnement", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "weekly", "title": "Canadian Ice Services - Ice Graph Tool", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "La collection de cartes r\u00e9gionales des Archives num\u00e9riques du SCG se compose de Cartes d'analyse hebdomadaire r\u00e9gionale des glaces de 1968 \u00e0 aujourd'hui, en format ArcGIS. Les cartes papier de 1968 \u00e0 1998 ont \u00e9t\u00e9 num\u00e9ris\u00e9es en format ArcGIS et l'ensemble de donn\u00e9es est actualis\u00e9 en temps r\u00e9el. Toutes les cartes pour l'Arctique canadien de l'est et de l'ouest, la baie d'Hudson, la C\u00f4te est du Canada et les Grands Lacs peuvent \u00eatre t\u00e9l\u00e9charg\u00e9es au moyen de l'interface de cartes en ligne.", "id": "", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2010-09-23", "time_period_coverage_start": "1968-01-01", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "http://www.ec.gc.ca/glaces-ice/default.asp?lang=Fr&n=D32C361E-1", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "2010-01-01", "language": "", "url": "http://www.ec.gc.ca/glaces-ice/default.asp?lang=En&n=D32C361E-1", "notes": "The CIS Digital Archive - Regional Charts collection consists of weekly Regional Ice Analysis Charts from 1968 to present in ArcGIS format. The paper charts from 1968 to 1998 were digitized in ArcGIS format and the dataset is updated in real-time. All charts for the Canadian Eastern and Western Arctic, the Hudson Bay, the East Coast of Canada, and the Great Lakes can be downloaded with the on-line charts interface.", "owner_org": "49E2ADF4-AD7A-43EB-85C8-6433D37ED62C", "keywords_fra": "\u00e9paisseur de la glace, Service canadien des glaces, ressources hydriques de l'arctique", "resource_type": "file", "department_number": ""}
{"portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": null, "keywords": "rainfall", "data_series_issue_identification": "", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "Nature and Environment  Nature et environnement", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "title": "Short-duration rainfall intesity-duration-frequency ", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Statistiques sur l'intensit\u00e9, la dur\u00e9e et la fr\u00e9quence (IDF) des pluies \u00e0 court terme sous forme de tableaux et de graphiques avec documentation pertinente pour 549 endroits au Canada. Ces fichiers peuvent \u00eatre t\u00e9l\u00e9charg\u00e9s pour chaque province ou territoire ou pour l'ensemble du Canada.\n", "id": "", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2010-04-22", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_f.html", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "language": "", "url": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_e.html", "notes": "Short-duration rainfall intensity-duration-frequency (IDF) statistics in the form of tables and graphs with accompanying documentation, for 549 locations across Canada. These files can be downloaded for each province, territory or for all of Canada.\n", "owner_org": "49E2ADF4-AD7A-43EB-85C8-6433D37ED62C", "keywords_fra": "rainfall", "resource_type": "file", "department_number": ""}
